  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat the oven and brown the duck legs</strong></p>\n<p>Set the oven to 160°C/ 140°C (fan)/ 325°F/ Gas 3 and boil a kettle.</p>\n<p>Season the <strong>duck</strong> all over with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then add to a cold, dry, wide-based <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid. (Or use a frying pan and an oven-proof dish covered with tin foil later!). Cook for 6-7 minutes on medium-high or until browned all over and the fat has rendered.</p>\n<p>Tip: brown the skin and render the fat to add flavour.</p>\n<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>duck legs</strong> to a plate and reserve the <strong>dish</strong> for later.</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1645.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
