            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1645.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare the vegetables and stock</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>(skins on). Peel and slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong>. <br /><br />Dissolve the <strong>beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and <strong>Just Add Wine sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>.</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1645.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1645.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1645.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1645.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1645.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Soften the vegetables</strong></p>\n<p>Discard some of the <strong>oil</strong> from the <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> so you're left with just 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>. Return it to a medium heat.</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 minutes or until starting to soften.</p>\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>beef stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 minutes.</p>",
